snippet: During a visit to Kiev, the vice president assured Ukrainian leaders that Russian cooperation in Syria would not change America’s position, and also pressed them to do more to battle corruption.
abstract: Vice Pres Joseph R Biden Jr tells Ukrainian leaders that United States will not sacrifice Ukraine in seeking Russian cooperation in Syria; says US supports them in conflict with pro-Russian separatists and promises more aid.
lead_paragraph: During a visit to Kiev, the vice president assured Ukrainian leaders that Russian cooperation in Syria would not change America’s position, and also pressed them to do more to battle corruption.

headline.main: Joe Biden Says U.S. Is Still Backing Ukraine
headline.print_headline: Biden Offers Ukraine Reassurance, Then Warning
